            "description": "Converted from SIGMA Rule.  Original Author: Rafal Piasecki SIGMA Title: Bpfdoor TCP Ports Redirect SIGMA Description: All TCP traffic on particular port from attacker is routed to different port. ex. '/sbin/iptables -t nat -D PREROUTING -p tcp -s 192.168.1.1 --dport 22 -j REDIRECT --to-ports 42392' The traffic looks like encrypted SSH communications going to TCP port 22, but in reality is being directed to the shell port once it hits the iptables rule for the attacker host only.   False positives: - Legitimate ports redirect  This rule may be covered under the Detection Rule License: https://ibm.biz/SigmaDetectionRuleLicense",
